{
  "texts": [
    "This means that the cosine similarity metric always returns a value between -1 and 1.",
    "A number of text tokenization schemes were tested (Supplementary Table 1).",
    "EchoCLIP was trained using text tokenized by a BPE tokenizer 27 pretrained on the GPT2 data corpus, which encoded echocardiography reports with a mean of 530.3 (±154.7) tokens per report.",
    "Due to the context length limit of 77 tokens imposed by fine-tuning from CLIP weights, EchoCLIP was trained on snippets of reports rather than their full text.",
    "For EchoCLIP-R, we noted that the echocardiography report text is often highly structured and repetitive, as they are typically generated in a 'fill-in-the-blank' fashion according to a predetermined template given to the cardiologist at the time of interpretation."
  ]
